As one begins to model their life, their perspectives, and their ambitions - think of the strength of trees🌲 Choose to focus on “Growing Down;” more rooted and stedfast, rather than growing to the sky. 
To grow up - something everyone feels so rushed to do - to chase successes when compared to others in our view and stampede toward the stereotypical “sky’s the limit” mentality of repeated success, may lead one to be “top heavy”. But a tree that has not grown deep into the ground’s rich hard soil will be uprooted with any type of bad weather. Without a strong fixed grasp on the Earth, without being fastened & rooted into ones foundation and the Earth’s core, the tree itself is weak. Instead of focusing on the fruits thy tree bears, focus on its roots. GROW DOWN. Plant yourself in GOD’s WILL. Plant yourself in knowledge, persistance, passion, self awareness, resilience, determination against all odds. Weather storms, cold fronts, rain showers, blazing heats, winds from nowhere and fall🌱🍁🌿. Grow down and your tree will grow strong, it will withstand any type of weather, and with time, bear bountiful fruits and flowers that bloom with every season. - Robert Ri’chard

2. : the magnitude of a quantity (such as force or power) per unit (as of area, charge, mass, or time)

3. : the measurable amount of a property, such as acute pressure, brightness, or a magnetic field.

Thank you for teaching me how to be of better service to the world around and especially to those I love. I will continue to strengthen my mind and my character and the environment I set up around me and the family in your honor. And thanks for the nerd genes🤓📡🚀

To being great husbands and examples of great men. Thanks for being smarter than me and stronger than me and more accomplished so that i have men to look up to! 

To my brothers-in-arms, you know who you are😉. Thanks for showing me how to win. And build businesses. Thanks for inviting me to your homes across the world with your families as one of yours - your brother. Forever in debted and I know this. Humbly, i appreciate yall’s greatness in my life. May we clink glasses and toast for life🥃
